**Week:** 5 | **Task:** 3

---

## Objective

Fine-tune a pretrained YOLOv8 model on the labeled MD trajectory dataset. Monitor training and validation loss curves to identify the optimal stopping epoch and avoid overfitting.

---

## Training Setup

```python
from ultralytics import YOLO

# Load pretrained YOLOv8 model (transfer learning)
model = YOLO("yolov8n.pt")  # nano variant for faster training

# Train on MD trajectory dataset
results = model.train(
    data="dataset_scaled.yaml",    # path to dataset config
    epochs=100,                    # high epoch count to observe loss curves
    imgsz=384,                     # matches scaled image width
    batch=16,                      # adjust based on GPU memory
    name="md_trajectory_v1",       # run name
    patience=20,                   # early stopping patience
    lr0=0.01,                      # initial learning rate
    lrf=0.001,                     # final learning rate
    optimizer="AdamW",
    augment=True,                  # data augmentation
    save=True,
    save_period=10,                # save checkpoint every 10 epochs
    device=0                       # GPU 0; use 'cpu' if no GPU
)
```

