## Loss Curves Analysis

Training produces per-epoch metrics saved to `results.csv`. Key columns:

| Column | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `train/box_loss` | Bounding box regression loss (train) |
| `train/cls_loss` | Classification loss (train) |
| `val/box_loss` | Bounding box regression loss (validation) |
| `val/cls_loss` | Classification loss (validation) |
| `metrics/mAP50` | Mean Average Precision at IoU=0.5 |

**Plot training curves:**

```python
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

df = pd.read_csv("runs/detect/md_trajectory_v1/results.csv")
df.columns = df.columns.str.strip()

fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 4))

# Box Loss
axes[0].plot(df["epoch"], df["train/box_loss"], label="Train Box Loss", color="blue")
axes[0].plot(df["epoch"], df["val/box_loss"], label="Val Box Loss", color="orange")
axes[0].set_title("Bounding Box Loss")
axes[0].set_xlabel("Epoch")
axes[0].legend()

# Classification Loss
axes[1].plot(df["epoch"], df["train/cls_loss"], label="Train Cls Loss", color="green")
axes[1].plot(df["epoch"], df["val/cls_loss"], label="Val Cls Loss", color="red")
axes[1].set_title("Classification Loss")
axes[1].set_xlabel("Epoch")
axes[1].legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig("loss_curves.png", dpi=150)
plt.show()
```

---

## Observed Training Behaviour

| Epoch Range | Behaviour |
|-------------|-----------|
| 1 – 30 | Both train and val loss decrease steadily |
| 30 – 55 | Val loss plateaus; train loss continues decreasing |
| 55+ | Val loss begins increasing → **overfitting onset** |

**Optimal stopping epoch: ~50** (where val loss is minimum)

`best.pt` is automatically saved at this point by Ultralytics.

